{
  "video_id": "6VRZdJl9GRk",
  "title": "Is \"Talking White\" Actually A Thing?",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 6520.0,
      "end_time": 8590.0,
      "text": "- Turns out, Americans are pretty good"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 8600.0,
      "end_time": 10660.0,
      "text": "at guessing your race just by hearing your voice."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 10660.0,
      "end_time": 12440.0,
      "text": "It's called, linguistic profiling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 12440.0,
      "end_time": 13639.0,
      "text": "and we all do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 13640.0,
      "end_time": 15450.0,
      "text": "There are certain auditory cues"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15450.0,
      "end_time": 18000.0,
      "text": "that give us subtle hints about who we're talking to."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 18000.0,
      "end_time": 20720.0,
      "text": "A lot of black American's speak what's referred to as,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 20720.0,
      "end_time": 24602.0,
      "text": "AAVE, or African American Vernacular English."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 24603.0,
      "end_time": 29290.0,
      "text": "- AAVE is non-rotic meaning, that like a British accent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 29290.0,
      "end_time": 32100.0,
      "text": "there are no \"R\" sounds at the end of words"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 32100.0,
      "end_time": 33310.0,
      "text": "or at the end of syllables."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 33310.0,
      "end_time": 35650.0,
      "text": "- John Flemming is a speech and dialect coach"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 35650.0,
      "end_time": 37739.0,
      "text": "for movies and video games."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 37740.0,
      "end_time": 40380.0,
      "text": "- Generally speaking, there's the \"th\" sounds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 40380.0,
      "end_time": 45100.0,
      "text": "the \"tha, tha\" and, \"the the,\" get replaced with something."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 45100.0,
      "end_time": 46900.0,
      "text": "Generally a \"T,\" or a \"D.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 46900.0,
      "end_time": 48430.0,
      "text": "There's a few other vowels and things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 48430.0,
      "end_time": 50100.0,
      "text": "but it kind of keeps going and going,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 50100.0,
      "end_time": 52410.0,
      "text": "and it gets kind of, into the weeds a bit."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 52410.0,
      "end_time": 54360.0,
      "text": "- When it comes to being on the phone though,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 54360.0,
      "end_time": 57300.0,
      "text": "black people will often try to sound more white."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 57300.0,
      "end_time": 58730.0,
      "text": "- Uh, yes, Mister Ribbon I would love"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 58730.0,
      "end_time": 60389.0,
      "text": "to have the opportunity to sit with you"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 60390.0,
      "end_time": 61960.0,
      "text": "to discuss some of our products."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 61960.0,
      "end_time": 63720.0,
      "text": "It's a form of code-switching."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 63720.0,
      "end_time": 65530.0,
      "text": "Or in this case, alternating between"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 65530.0,
      "end_time": 66530.0,
      "text": "two different dialects."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 66530.0,
      "end_time": 68730.0,
      "text": "- He tried to grab me by my collar, right."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 68730.0,
      "end_time": 69970.0,
      "text": "That's when I ---"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 69970.0,
      "end_time": 70830.0,
      "text": "Uh, good morning."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 70830.0,
      "end_time": 72630.0,
      "text": "Customer service, my name is Philip."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 73830.0,
      "end_time": 75800.0,
      "text": "- Black people talking white"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 75800.0,
      "end_time": 77490.0,
      "text": "is having a real moment in media right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 77490.0,
      "end_time": 80390.0,
      "text": "\"Sorry To Bother You\", is a movie about a black salesman"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 80400.0,
      "end_time": 81400.0,
      "text": "who's career only takes off"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 81400.0,
      "end_time": 83280.0,
      "text": "when he starts talking white."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 83280.0,
      "end_time": 85920.0,
      "text": "- You wanna make some money here, use your white voice."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 85920.0,
      "end_time": 89300.0,
      "text": "Hey, Mister Kramer, this is Langston from Regal View."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 90150.0,
      "end_time": 91820.0,
      "text": "- [Manny] And \"BlacKkKlansman\", is a movie about"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 91820.0,
      "end_time": 94449.0,
      "text": "a black detective who infiltrates the KKK"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 94450.0,
      "end_time": 97290.0,
      "text": "by pretending to be white over the phone."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 97290.0,
      "end_time": 99270.0,
      "text": "- God bless White America."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 99270.0,
      "end_time": 100920.0,
      "text": "- The idea is to speak in what's called"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 100920.0,
      "end_time": 102300.0,
      "text": "the standard accent."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 102300.0,
      "end_time": 104380.0,
      "text": "- The standard accent is the one spoken"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 104380.0,
      "end_time": 107119.0,
      "text": "by the majority group, or the socially advantaged group."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 107120.0,
      "end_time": 109696.0,
      "text": "- [Manny] Olivia Kang is a psychologist at Harvard."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 109696.0,
      "end_time": 111820.0,
      "text": "She's working on a project that explores"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 111820.0,
      "end_time": 113490.0,
      "text": "the hidden biases we hold."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 113490.0,
      "end_time": 115690.0,
      "text": "- If you speak with a standard accent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 115690.0,
      "end_time": 117808.0,
      "text": "you're judged as being more intelligent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 117808.0,
      "end_time": 120870.0,
      "text": "more competent, more credible, more hireable."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 120870.0,
      "end_time": 124370.0,
      "text": "Now, having a regional accent, or a non-standard accent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 124370.0,
      "end_time": 125900.0,
      "text": "now you're not getting those advantages."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 125900.0,
      "end_time": 129500.0,
      "text": "You're seen as less credible, or less hireable."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 129500.0,
      "end_time": 130860.0,
      "text": "- These biases are implicit."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 130860.00000000001,
      "end_time": 133550.0,
      "text": "This isn't Charlotesville tiki-torch racism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 133550.0,
      "end_time": 135350.0,
      "text": "it's much more discreet than that."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 135350.0,
      "end_time": 138130.0,
      "text": "- The most basic way of understanding implicit bias"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 138130.0,
      "end_time": 141760.0,
      "text": "is by thinking about the associations we make."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 141760.0,
      "end_time": 144399.0,
      "text": "If two things occur together over and over again"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 144400.0,
      "end_time": 147160.0,
      "text": "in our experience, we link them together."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 147160.0,
      "end_time": 150790.0,
      "text": "- Salt and pepper, day and night, bread and butter."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 150790.0,
      "end_time": 153900.0,
      "text": "These types of associations are helpful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 153900.0,
      "end_time": 154670.0,
      "text": "but there are some that aren't."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 154670.0,
      "end_time": 156350.0,
      "text": "Now, if I say the word, genius,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 156350.0,
      "end_time": 157609.0,
      "text": "you're probably thinking of some"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 157610.0,
      "end_time": 159600.0,
      "text": "collectors edition white dude."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 159600.0,
      "end_time": 161472.0,
      "text": "Now, if I say the word criminal..."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 163940.0,
      "end_time": 166530.0,
      "text": "- Voices aren't just sounds."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 166530.0,
      "end_time": 169600.0,
      "text": "In a lot of ways they're auditory faces."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 169600.0,
      "end_time": 172320.0,
      "text": "So, when you hear a voice, you can in some sense"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 172320.0,
      "end_time": 174290.0,
      "text": "piece together what the person on the other end"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 174290.0,
      "end_time": 176400.0,
      "text": "of the phone, can look like."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 176400.0,
      "end_time": 178350.0,
      "text": "Roughly how old they are, their gender,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 178350.0,
      "end_time": 180170.0,
      "text": "where they come from."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 180170.0,
      "end_time": 181359.0,
      "text": "But, the interesting thing is that"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 181360.0,
      "end_time": 184240.0,
      "text": "you can also form impressions about character."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 184240.0,
      "end_time": 186220.0,
      "text": "So, how intelligent someone is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 186220.0,
      "end_time": 189210.0,
      "text": "how competent, how likable, how trustworthy."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 189210.0,
      "end_time": 193200.0,
      "text": "And, these impressions can be flawed, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 193200.0,
      "end_time": 195600.0,
      "text": "A lot of these things might have"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 195600.0,
      "end_time": 197810.0,
      "text": "a basis in your implicit biases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 197810.0,
      "end_time": 198880.0,
      "text": "or things that you've heard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 198880.0,
      "end_time": 201900.0,
      "text": "portrayals you've seen on television."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 201900.0,
      "end_time": 205200.0,
      "text": "And so, when people are doing something,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 205200.0,
      "end_time": 206810.0,
      "text": "like conducting a voice interview,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 206810.0,
      "end_time": 210150.0,
      "text": "often the implicit biases they have about voice"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 210150.0,
      "end_time": 212608.0,
      "text": "can influence the decisions that they're making."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 212608.0,
      "end_time": 215730.0,
      "text": "- Every black American is bilingual."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 215730.0,
      "end_time": 220113.0,
      "text": "We speak street vernacular, and we speak job interview."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 222170.0,
      "end_time": 224970.0,
      "text": "- In order to combat some of these implicit biases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 224970.0,
      "end_time": 227440.0,
      "text": "black people, myself included, try to sound"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 227440.0,
      "end_time": 229100.0,
      "text": "as white as possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 229100.0,
      "end_time": 231980.0,
      "text": "I sound like Bill Gates impersonating your mailman."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 231980.0,
      "end_time": 232929.0,
      "text": "Why hello there."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 232930.0,
      "end_time": 235100.0,
      "text": "I'm wondering if there are any positions available."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 235100.0,
      "end_time": 236570.0,
      "text": "Oh no, I don't mind waiting."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 236570.0,
      "end_time": 238660.0,
      "text": "But, does changing your voice actually work."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 238660.0,
      "end_time": 241490.0,
      "text": "A study in 2001 found that landlords"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 241490.0,
      "end_time": 243370.0,
      "text": "would make racist snap judgements"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 243370.0,
      "end_time": 245470.0,
      "text": "to callers with certain dialects."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 245470.0,
      "end_time": 247870.0,
      "text": "Compared with whites, blacks were less likely"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 247870.0,
      "end_time": 250180.0,
      "text": "to get call backs, less likely to be told"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 250180.0,
      "end_time": 251700.0,
      "text": "there was an apartment available,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 251700.0,
      "end_time": 254329.0,
      "text": "and more likely to get their credit questioned."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 254330.0,
      "end_time": 257180.0,
      "text": "However, blacks who code-switched fared better"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 257180.0,
      "end_time": 258950.0,
      "text": "than those who didn't."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 258950.0,
      "end_time": 261500.0,
      "text": "Code-switching helps in other areas too."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 261500.0,
      "end_time": 263390.0,
      "text": "- Actually Don Lemon is a very good example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 263390.0,
      "end_time": 266490.0,
      "text": "because to become this main host that he is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 266490.0,
      "end_time": 268700.0,
      "text": "he's talked about how he had to change -"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 268700.0,
      "end_time": 270640.0,
      "text": "because he's from New Orleans - and he consciously"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 270640.0,
      "end_time": 274800.0,
      "text": "had to change his accent for the sake of moving up at CNN."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 274800.0,
      "end_time": 278000.0,
      "text": "- The president of the United States is racist."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 278000.0,
      "end_time": 280240.0,
      "text": "- Instead of changing the way we speak,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 280240.0,
      "end_time": 282530.0,
      "text": "maybe we should change the way we listen."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 282530.0,
      "end_time": 284859.0,
      "text": "I might be able to tell your race from your voice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 284860.0,
      "end_time": 287920.0,
      "text": "but that doesn't tell me anything about your character."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 287920.0,
      "end_time": 289229.0,
      "text": "There's tons of black mailmen."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 289229.0,
      "end_time": 290931.0,
      "text": "- [Delisa] Too many."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 290931.0,
      "end_time": 292378.0,
      "text": "My dad is a black mailman."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 292379.0,
      "end_time": 295540.0,
      "text": "So don't be talking about BS like that, 'cuz my dad"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 295540.0,
      "end_time": 297860.0,
      "text": "will run up on you real quick."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 297860.0,
      "end_time": 299600.0,
      "text": "- I don't want no smoke."
    }
  ]
}